               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donors; groups of lines on the incipit page of Text I-2; incipit of all other texts, incipit of (sub)sections of texts and section numbers of Text I-2; first word of each strophe of Texts I-3, II-2, II-6, II-7; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>All miracles of Mary are numbered.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-1 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Maryam Mariham ʾǝmmu lä-ʾǝgziʾǝnä ʾIyäsus Krǝstos kähali ... "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of our Lord, Jesus Christ the Almighty ..." (fol. 11v) (cp. ChRep no. 373)</note>
                     <note>- Sälam läki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Maryam ʾǝmmä mädḫǝn wä-ʾǝmmä bǝrhan ... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (fols. 11v l.18-13r).</note>
                     <note>- a shorter version of Ṣälotä zä-yǝbl ʾǝmqǝdmä yanbǝbu täʾamriha lä-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝnä Maryam ... "Prayer recited before reading the Miracles of Mary ..." (fol. 14v)</note>
                     <note>- Excerpt from the Gospel of John (Jn. 19:25-27) (fol. 14v).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text II-2 is also known as Mälkǝʿa ʾEdom "Image of Edom".</note>
                     <note>Text II-3 is the first homily from Dǝrsanä Mikaʾel.</note>
                     <note>Text II-7 is known as Mälkǝʿa śǝʿǝl "Image of the Icon" within the Mälkǝʿa gubaʾe "Collection of Images".</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
